      "$comment": "15 variants in 5 Rarity × 3 Size grid at (80,1740). Pill (radius/pill), HUG width, fixed h per size: Sm=20 / Md=24 / Lg=28. Bg = solid bound to color/rarity/{name} with paint opacity 0.15 (alpha-tint mirroring DomainTag — zero new color tokens). Border = same rarity color at full opacity, 1px INSIDE. ◆ + 'Lv 1' text at full opacity in rarity color. Sora SemiBold override on top of size-appropriate text style (Sm=Small, Md=Caption, Lg=Body). Padding-x: Sm=spacing/6, Md=spacing/10 (new primitive, VariableID:62:2), Lg=spacing/12. Gap: Sm/Md=spacing/4, Lg=spacing/6. Elevation/1 shadow on every variant. Level TEXT prop default 'Lv 1' — single shared default works because all 15 variants have identical text content (DomainTag's per-variant text gotcha does NOT apply here). GOTCHA: setBoundVariableForPaint + spread+opacity pattern did NOT persist opacity 0.15 on first pass — required a follow-up read-modify-write pass (v.fills.map(p => ({...p, opacity:0.15}))). Cause unclear; prior atoms with same pattern (DomainTag) persisted correctly. For future alpha-tinted atoms, verify fill.opacity after creation and apply read-modify-write fix-up if needed.",
